p; gluteus minimus externally rotates the hip","Gluteus maximus adducts the hip; gluteus minimus abducts the hip","Gluteus maximus flexes the hip; gluteus minimus extends the hip"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe gluteal muscles are a group of three muscles which make up the buttocks: the gluteus maximus, gluteus medius, and gluteus minimus. These muscles are important for various movements of the hip joint.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe primary function of the \u003Cstrong\u003Egluteus maximus\u003C/strong\u003E is to extend the hip, which is crucial for movements such as rising from a sitting position, climbing stairs, and running. In contrast, the \u003Cstrong\u003Egluteus minimus\u003C/strong\u003E primarily functions to abduct the hip, which is important for stabilising the pelvis during walking and preventing the opposite side of the pelvis from dropping.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EGluteus maximus abducts the hip\u003C/strong\u003E - The gluteus maximus is not primarily involved in hip abduction\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EGluteus maximus internally rotates the hip\u003C/strong\u003E - The gluteus maximus is involved in external rotation, not internal\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EGluteus maximus flexes the hip\u003C/strong\u003E - The gluteus maximus extends the hip, not flexes\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EGluteus maximus adducts the hip\u003C/strong\u003E - The gluteus maximus does not primarily adduct the hip\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The gluteus maximus is primarily responsible for hip extension and external rotation.","The gluteus minimus is primarily responsible for hip abduction and internal rotation.","Both muscles play important roles in stabilising the pelvis during locomotion."],"references":["Sud, A., \u0026 Ranjan, R. (2018). Textbook of Orthopaedics, -E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Singh, V. (2018). Textbook of Anatomy Abdomen and Lower Limb; Volume II (Vol. 2). Elsevier Health Sciences","Cantrell AJ, Imonugo O, Varacallo M. Anatomy, Bony Pelvis and Lower Limb: Leg Bones. [Updated 2023 Aug 14]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK537024/","Raftery A. General Anatomy and Musculoskeletal System. Ann R Coll Surg Engl. 2006 Jul;88(4):425. doi: 10.1308/003588406X114802d. PMCID: PMC1964629","Chaudhry SR, Nahian A, Chaudhry K. Anatomy, Abdomen and Pelvis, Pelvis. [Updated 2023 Jul 25]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK482258/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65303"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18312"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65303","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/65303"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-16T20:08:38+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-16T20:09:10+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11030"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80032"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior,